references: Table 3 displays the recommendation performance for Top-1 recommendations, measured by Precision@1 and Recall@1. These metrics assess the quality of recommendations when only one item is suggested. Since only one item is recommended, NDCG@1 simplifies to Precision@1. X-Reflect demonstrates strong performance in Top-1 recommendations, achieving the highest Precision@1 and Recall@1 on the Amazon-Software dataset, and the highest Recall@1 with the second-highest Precision@1 on MovieLens-1M. KAR (Xi et al. 2023) achieves the highest Precision@1 on MovieLens-1M, likely because it uses open-world knowledge to enrich item descriptions. For movies, unique characteristics that are better represented as knowledge may allow KAR to precisely augment special information, making it particularly effective in Top-1 recommendations. However, as seen in the Top-10 recommendation results, KAR’s performance diminishes, potentially due to its limited ability to enrich general information effectively. Tables 5 and 4 show the corresponding recommendation performance. With LLaVA as the backbone, X-Reflect continues to outperform other prompting baselines. When InternLM is used as the backbone, our method remains one of the top-performing frameworks, achieving the highest Precision@10 across both datasets and excelling on the Amazon-Software dataset.

When InternLM is used as the backbone, our method remains one of the top-performing frameworks, achieving the highest Precision@10 across both datasets and excelling on the Amazon-Software dataset.
